race.comment: ZIG ZAG MAN (7) has an excellent record here having never missed the placings in eight starts, including seven wins. Hit the frame latest (29.72) when second at Wentworth Park in a NG. Rates on top and should go close. REBORN HOSTILITY (2) thrives over the longer races. Was a strong winner last time (35.43) over 622m at this track in a Grade 5. Has never been out of the money in four starts this distance. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Likely to be in the finish. MAKE THEM CRY (6) goes very well this trip starting 13 times for six wins and five minors. In the money last time at Wentworth Park (42.80) in a Grade 5, finishing a 0.8 lengths third. Looks one of the chances. WEST ROCK CASEY (4) is worth including after a top-three finish from the same draw most recently.
